---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Button from '../components/Button.astro'
import {VIKUNJA_CLOUD_LINK} from '../helpers/vikunjaCloudLink'
---
<Layout title="Convince Your Boss" description="Everything you need to bring Vikunja to your team at work. Cost comparison, security posture, deployment options, and a one-pager you can forward.">
    <main class="max-w-(--breakpoint-xl) mx-auto px-4 md:px-0">
        <div class="pt-32 pb-8 px-4 text-center">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-display">
                Bring Vikunja to work.
            </h1>
            <p class="mt-4 text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-balance">
                You already use Vikunja at home. Here's everything you need to make the case for your team.
            </p>
        </div>

        <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-16">
            <h2 class="font-display text-3xl mb-6">The pitch in 30 seconds</h2>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-sm p-8 text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                <p>
                    Vikunja is open-source task management that runs on your infrastructure.
                    It replaces Todoist, Trello, or Asana for teams that need full control over their data.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    Your team gets lists, Kanban boards, Gantt charts, and table views,
                    with shared projects, assignments, and real-time collaboration.
                    Enterprise features like a dedicated instance, admin tools,
                    and a GDPR data processing agreement are available at any team size. No minimum seat count.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    It's made and hosted in the EU, openly licensed under the AGPLv3,
                    and completely bootstrapped. Funded by users, not VCs.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-20">
            <h2 class="font-display text-3xl mb-6">Why switch from what we already use?</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-sm p-6">
                    <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-3">Your data stays yours</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                        Self-host on your own infrastructure or use our EU-hosted cloud.
                        No data leaves your control. No US cloud provider in the chain.
                        Full GDPR compliance with a data processing agreement available.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-sm p-6">
                    <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-3">No vendor lock-in</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                        Open-source under the AGPLv3 means you can read every line of code,
                        export your data anytime, and switch hosting providers without losing anything.
                        You're never locked into a contract you can't leave.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-sm p-6">
                    <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-3">Enterprise features without the enterprise price tag</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                        Dedicated instances, admin user management, and GDPR contracts
                        don't require 25+ users or a six-figure budget.
                        Your compliance requirements don't care how many employees you have.
                        Neither does Vikunja's pricing.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-sm p-6">
                    <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-3">One tool, four views</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                        List, Kanban, Gantt, and Table. Your team doesn't have to pick one workflow.
                        Developers can use Kanban while project managers use Gantt,
                        all looking at the same data.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-20">
            <h2 class="font-display text-3xl mb-6">Cost comparison</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
                For a team of 15 people, billed yearly:
            </p>
            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
                    <thead>
                        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                            <th class="py-3 px-4 font-display text-lg"></th>
                            <th class="py-3 px-4 font-display text-lg">Vikunja Self-Hosted</th>
                            <th class="py-3 px-4 font-display text-lg">Vikunja Cloud (Org)</th>
                            <th class="py-3 px-4 font-display text-lg">Todoist Business</th>
                            <th class="py-3 px-4 font-display text-lg">Asana Premium</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800">
                            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Annual cost</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-display text-xl">0 &euro;</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-display text-xl">750 &euro;</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-500">~1,440 &euro;</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-500">~1,978 &euro;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800">
                            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Self-hostable</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">Yes</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">&mdash;</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">&mdash;</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">&mdash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800">
                            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Open source</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">Yes</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">Yes</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">&mdash;</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">&mdash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800">
                            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">EU data residency</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">Your choice</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">Yes</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">&mdash;</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">&mdash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Vendor lock-in</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">None</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">None</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">High</td>
                            <td class="py-3 px-4">High</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-4">
                Competitor prices based on published pricing pages as of April 2026. Your actual cost may vary.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-20">
            <h2 class="font-display text-3xl mb-6">Security and compliance</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-display text-lg mb-2">Open source</h3>
                    <p>
                        Every line of Vikunja's code is publicly auditable under the AGPLv3.
                        No hidden telemetry, no proprietary black boxes.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-display text-lg mb-2">Made and hosted in the EU</h3>
                    <p>
                        Vikunja is built in Germany and hosted on EU infrastructure.
                        No data transfers to the US. No CLOUD Act exposure.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-display text-lg mb-2">GDPR-ready</h3>
                    <p>
                        Data processing agreements are available on the Enterprise plan.
                        Self-hosted instances give you complete control over data residency.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-display text-lg mb-2">Responsible disclosure</h3>
                    <p>
                        Security vulnerabilities are handled through a
                        <a href="/security" class="underline">responsible disclosure process</a>
                        with published advisories and CVEs.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-20">
            <h2 class="font-display text-3xl mb-6">Deployment options</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
                Pick what fits your team's infrastructure:
            </p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                <div class="border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-sm p-6">
                    <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-2">Docker</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                        Single container, one command. The fastest way to get running.
                        Works on any server with Docker installed.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-sm p-6">
                    <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-2">Kubernetes</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                        Helm chart available for production Kubernetes clusters.
                        Scale horizontally as your team grows.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-sm p-6">
                    <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-2">Vikunja Cloud</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                        Don't want to manage infrastructure? We'll host it for you
                        on EU servers. Enterprise plans get a dedicated instance.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-20">
            <h2 class="font-display text-3xl mb-6">Run a team pilot</h2>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-sm p-8">
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
                    The best way to evaluate Vikunja is to use it with your team for two weeks. Here's how:
                </p>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Pick 5&ndash;10 people</strong>:
                        a mix of roles that represent how your team actually works.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Set up a test instance</strong>:
                        <a href="/install" class="underline">self-host with Docker</a> in 5 minutes,
                        or start a <a href={VIKUNJA_CLOUD_LINK} class="underline">free 14-day Cloud trial</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Import existing tasks</strong>:
                        bring in your data from Todoist, Trello, or Microsoft To-Do.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Use it for real work</strong>:
                        run your actual sprint, project, or team tasks through Vikunja for two weeks.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Evaluate</strong>:
                        does it cover your workflow? Is your team using it without being reminded?
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-20 mb-20 text-center">
            <h2 class="font-display text-3xl mb-4">Ready to get started?</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">
                Have questions about Enterprise or need help scoping a pilot?
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center items-center">
                <Button href="/pro">
                    Vikunja Pro
                </Button>
                <Button href="/pricing" class="bg-gray-200! text-gray-800! dark:bg-gray-700! dark:text-gray-200!">
                    See pricing
                </Button>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>
